---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Simulation | Jack Corbin" hideParticles={true}>
  <div class="page-container">
    <h1 class="page-title">// simulation</h1>
    <p class="text-dim intro">
      Control Barrier Functions (CBFs) enforce safety constraints by solving a QP that minimally
      modifies each agent's nominal velocity to satisfy ḣ + α·h ≥ 0. Move your cursor
      (or touch) to be the obstacle.
    </p>

    <div class="terminal-window">
      <div class="terminal-titlebar">
        <span class="window-dots">
          <span class="dot dot-red"></span>
          <span class="dot dot-yellow"></span>
          <span class="dot dot-green"></span>
        </span>
        <span class="terminal-title">jack@corbin:~$ ./cbf_sim</span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body" id="terminal-body">
        <canvas id="sim-canvas"></canvas>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="controls-panel">
      <div class="controls-grid">
        <div class="slider-row">
          <label class="slider-label" for="sl-agents"># agents</label>
          <input type="range" id="sl-agents" min="5" max="100" value="30" step="1" />
          <span class="slider-value" id="sv-agents">30</span>
        </div>
        <div class="slider-row">
          <label class="slider-label" for="sl-speed"># nominal_speed</label>
          <input type="range" id="sl-speed" min="0.25" max="3.0" value="1.125" step="0.125" />
          <span class="slider-value" id="sv-speed">1.125</span>
        </div>
        <div class="slider-row">
          <label class="slider-label" for="sl-radius"># obstacle_radius</label>
          <input type="range" id="sl-radius" min="30" max="200" value="100" step="5" />
          <span class="slider-value" id="sv-radius">100</span>
        </div>
        <div class="slider-row">
          <label class="slider-label" for="sl-alpha"># alpha (CBF gain)</label>
          <input type="range" id="sl-alpha" min="0.1" max="10.0" value="2.0" step="0.1" />
          <span class="slider-value" id="sv-alpha">2.0</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <button class="reset-btn" id="reset-btn">[reset]</button>
    </div>

    <div class="math-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">// formulation</h2>

      <div class="math-block">
        <h3 class="math-heading">System model</h3>
        <p class="math-text">
          Each agent is a single-integrator: <span class="math">ẋ = u</span>, where
          <span class="math">x ∈ ℝ²</span> is position and <span class="math">u ∈ ℝ²</span>
          is the control (velocity) input we choose each timestep.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="math-block">
        <h3 class="math-heading">Barrier function</h3>
        <p class="math-text">
          Given a circular obstacle at <span class="math">o</span> with safe radius
          <span class="math">r</span>, define the barrier function:
        </p>
        <div class="math-display">h(x) = ‖x − o‖ − r</div>
        <p class="math-text">
          The set <span class="math">&#123;x : h(x) ≥ 0&#125;</span> is the safe region.
          When <span class="math">h &gt; 0</span> the agent is outside the obstacle;
          <span class="math">h = 0</span> is the boundary; <span class="math">h &lt; 0</span>
          means violation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="math-block">
        <h3 class="math-heading">CBF condition</h3>
        <p class="math-text">
          To keep the system safe, we require the barrier to satisfy:
        </p>
        <div class="math-display">ḣ(x, u) + α · h(x) ≥ 0</div>
        <p class="math-text">
          Expanding the time derivative: <span class="math">ḣ = ∇h · u</span>, where the
          gradient <span class="math">∇h = (x − o) / ‖x − o‖</span> is the unit normal
          pointing away from the obstacle. The parameter <span class="math">α &gt; 0</span>
          controls how permissive the barrier is &mdash; larger α allows agents to cut closer
          before deflecting, while smaller α forces earlier, more conservative avoidance.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="math-block">
        <h3 class="math-heading">Quadratic program</h3>
        <p class="math-text">
          Each agent has a nominal (desired) velocity <span class="math">u_nom</span> from
          its wander behavior. We find the closest safe velocity by solving:
        </p>
        <div class="math-display">
          min<sub>u</sub> ‖u − u_nom‖²<br/>
          s.t. ∇h · u + α · h(x) ≥ 0
        </div>
        <p class="math-text">
          This is a QP with a single linear constraint on a quadratic cost. If the nominal
          input already satisfies the constraint, it passes through unchanged. Otherwise,
          the solution projects onto the constraint boundary.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="math-block">
        <h3 class="math-heading">Closed-form solution</h3>
        <p class="math-text">
          Let <span class="math">a = ∇h</span> (unit normal) and
          <span class="math">b = α · h(x)</span>. Evaluate the constraint at the nominal:
        </p>
        <div class="math-display">φ = a · u_nom + b</div>
        <p class="math-text">If <span class="math">φ ≥ 0</span>, the nominal is safe and
          <span class="math">u* = u_nom</span>. Otherwise, the optimal Lagrange multiplier
          is <span class="math">λ = −φ / (a · a) = −φ</span> (since
          <span class="math">‖a‖ = 1</span>), giving:
        </p>
        <div class="math-display">u* = u_nom − φ · ∇h</div>
        <p class="math-text">
          This is the minimum-norm correction &mdash; the agent deviates from its desired
          path only as much as needed to stay safe.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const canvas = document.getElementById('sim-canvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
  const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;
  const terminalBody = document.getElementById('terminal-body')!;

  // --- Parameters (mutable) ---
  const DEFAULTS = {
    agents: 30,
    speed: 1.125,
    radius: 100,
    alpha: 2.0,
  };

  let numAgents = DEFAULTS.agents;
  let nominalSpeed = DEFAULTS.speed;
  let obstacleRadius = DEFAULTS.radius;
  let alpha = DEFAULTS.alpha;
  const SAFETY_MARGIN = 20;
  const CONNECTION_DIST = 120;

  // --- Slider bindings ---
  const sliders: Record<string, { input: HTMLInputElement; display: HTMLElement; key: keyof typeof DEFAULTS }> = {
    agents:   { input: document.getElementById('sl-agents') as HTMLInputElement, display: document.getElementById('sv-agents')!, key: 'agents' },
    speed:    { input: document.getElementById('sl-speed') as HTMLInputElement, display: document.getElementById('sv-speed')!, key: 'speed' },
    radius:   { input: document.getElementById('sl-radius') as HTMLInputElement, display: document.getElementById('sv-radius')!, key: 'radius' },
    alpha:    { input: document.getElementById('sl-alpha') as HTMLInputElement, display: document.getElementById('sv-alpha')!, key: 'alpha' },
  };

  function syncFromSliders() {
    const newCount = parseInt(sliders.agents.input.value);
    nominalSpeed = parseFloat(sliders.speed.input.value);
    obstacleRadius = parseFloat(sliders.radius.input.value);
    alpha = parseFloat(sliders.alpha.input.value);

    sliders.agents.display.textContent = String(newCount);
    sliders.speed.display.textContent = nominalSpeed.toFixed(3);
    sliders.radius.display.textContent = String(obstacleRadius);
    sliders.alpha.display.textContent = alpha.toFixed(1);

    // Incremental agent add/remove
    if (newCount > numAgents) {
      for (let i = numAgents; i < newCount; i++) {
        agents.push(createAgent());
      }
    } else if (newCount < numAgents) {
      agents.length = newCount;
    }
    numAgents = newCount;
  }

  for (const s of Object.values(sliders)) {
    s.input.addEventListener('input', syncFromSliders);
  }

  document.getElementById('reset-btn')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    sliders.agents.input.value = String(DEFAULTS.agents);
    sliders.speed.input.value = String(DEFAULTS.speed);
    sliders.radius.input.value = String(DEFAULTS.radius);
    sliders.alpha.input.value = String(DEFAULTS.alpha);
    syncFromSliders();
  });

  // --- Theme ---
  let primaryColor = '';
  let primaryRgb = '';
  let bgColor = '';

  function readThemeColors() {
    const s = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement);
    primaryColor = s.getPropertyValue('--primary').trim();
    primaryRgb = s.getPropertyValue('--primary-rgb').trim();
    bgColor = s.getPropertyValue('--bg').trim();
  }
  readThemeColors();
  window.addEventListener('themechange', readThemeColors);

  // --- Canvas sizing ---
  let cw = 0;
  let ch = 0;
  const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;

  function resizeCanvas() {
    const rect = terminalBody.getBoundingClientRect();
    cw = rect.width;
    ch = rect.height;
    canvas.width = cw * dpr;
    canvas.height = ch * dpr;
    ctx.setTransform(dpr, 0, 0, dpr, 0, 0);
  }

  const ro = new ResizeObserver(resizeCanvas);
  ro.observe(terminalBody);
  resizeCanvas();

  // --- Mouse / touch ---
  let mouseX = -9999;
  let mouseY = -9999;
  let virtualAngle = 0;
  let hasTouch = false;
  const isMobile = window.innerWidth < 768;

  canvas.addEventListener('mousemove', (e) => {
    const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
    mouseX = e.clientX - rect.left;
    mouseY = e.clientY - rect.top;
  });

  canvas.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
    mouseX = -9999;
    mouseY = -9999;
  });

  canvas.addEventListener('touchstart', (e) => {
    hasTouch = true;
    updateTouch(e);
  }, { passive: true });

  canvas.addEventListener('touchmove', (e) => {
    updateTouch(e);
  }, { passive: true });

  canvas.addEventListener('touchend', () => {
    hasTouch = false;
    mouseX = -9999;
    mouseY = -9999;
  });

  function updateTouch(e: TouchEvent) {
    const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
    const t = e.touches[0];
    mouseX = t.clientX - rect.left;
    mouseY = t.clientY - rect.top;
  }

  // --- Agents ---
  interface Agent {
    x: number;
    y: number;
    vx: number;
    vy: number;
    targetAngle: number;
  }

  let agents: Agent[] = [];

  function createAgent(): Agent {
    const angle = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
    return {
      x: Math.random() * (cw || 600),
      y: Math.random() * (ch || 400),
      vx: Math.cos(angle) * 0.5,
      vy: Math.sin(angle) * 0.5,
      targetAngle: angle,
    };
  }

  function initAgents() {
    agents = [];
    for (let i = 0; i < numAgents; i++) {
      agents.push(createAgent());
    }
  }

  function getObstacle(): [number, number] {
    if (isMobile && !hasTouch) {
      virtualAngle += 0.005;
      const cx = cw / 2 + Math.cos(virtualAngle) * cw * 0.2;
      const cy = ch / 2 + Math.sin(virtualAngle * 0.7) * ch * 0.15;
      return [cx, cy];
    }
    return [mouseX, mouseY];
  }

  // --- Simulation loop ---
  let obstacleX = -9999;
  let obstacleY = -9999;

  function update() {
    const rSafe = obstacleRadius + SAFETY_MARGIN;
    const [ox, oy] = getObstacle();
    obstacleX = ox;
    obstacleY = oy;

    for (const agent of agents) {
      // 1. Compute nominal control (wander behavior)
      agent.targetAngle += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.3;
      let ux = agent.vx + Math.cos(agent.targetAngle) * 0.05;
      let uy = agent.vy + Math.sin(agent.targetAngle) * 0.05;

      // Clamp nominal to desired speed
      const uNomSpeed = Math.sqrt(ux * ux + uy * uy);
      if (uNomSpeed > nominalSpeed) {
        ux = ux / uNomSpeed * nominalSpeed;
        uy = uy / uNomSpeed * nominalSpeed;
      }

      // 2. CBF-QP: min ||u - u_nom||^2  s.t.  ∇h·u + α·h ≥ 0
      const dx = agent.x - ox;
      const dy = agent.y - oy;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);

      if (dist > 0 && dist < rSafe * 3) {
        const nx = dx / dist;  // ∇h (unit normal)
        const ny = dy / dist;
        const h = dist - rSafe; // barrier value

        // Scale α by 1/rSafe so pixel-scale h and velocity-scale u are comparable
        const phi = (ux * nx + uy * ny) + (alpha / rSafe) * h; // constraint value

        if (phi < 0) {
          // Project: u* = u_nom - phi * ∇h  (since ||∇h||² = 1)
          ux -= phi * nx;
          uy -= phi * ny;
        }
      }

      // 3. Integrate (no post-CBF speed clamp)
      agent.vx = ux;
      agent.vy = uy;
      agent.x += agent.vx;
      agent.y += agent.vy;

      // Wrap
      if (agent.x < 0) agent.x += cw;
      if (agent.x > cw) agent.x -= cw;
      if (agent.y < 0) agent.y += ch;
      if (agent.y > ch) agent.y -= ch;
    }
  }

  function draw() {
    // Trail clear using theme bg
    const bgRgba = bgColor ? bgColor : '#0a0a0a';
    ctx.fillStyle = hexToRgba(bgRgba, 0.15);
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, cw, ch);

    // Connection lines (skip if > 60 agents for performance)
    if (numAgents <= 60) {
      for (let i = 0; i < agents.length; i++) {
        for (let j = i + 1; j < agents.length; j++) {
          const dx = agents[i].x - agents[j].x;
          const dy = agents[i].y - agents[j].y;
          const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);
          if (dist < CONNECTION_DIST) {
            const a = (1 - dist / CONNECTION_DIST) * 0.15;
            ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${primaryRgb}, ${a})`;
            ctx.lineWidth = 0.5;
            ctx.beginPath();
            ctx.moveTo(agents[i].x, agents[i].y);
            ctx.lineTo(agents[j].x, agents[j].y);
            ctx.stroke();
          }
        }
      }
    }

    // Obstacle circles
    const showCircle = isMobile || obstacleX !== -9999;
    if (showCircle) {
      const rSafe = obstacleRadius + SAFETY_MARGIN;
      ctx.setLineDash([6, 4]);

      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(obstacleX, obstacleY, obstacleRadius, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${primaryRgb}, 0.3)`;
      ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      ctx.stroke();

      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(obstacleX, obstacleY, rSafe, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${primaryRgb}, 0.15)`;
      ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      ctx.stroke();

      ctx.setLineDash([]);
    }

    // Agents
    for (const agent of agents) {
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(agent.x, agent.y, 2, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.fillStyle = primaryColor;
      ctx.shadowColor = primaryColor;
      ctx.shadowBlur = 8;
      ctx.fill();
    }
    ctx.shadowBlur = 0;
  }

  function hexToRgba(hex: string, a: number): string {
    // Handle #rrggbb
    if (hex.startsWith('#') && hex.length === 7) {
      const r = parseInt(hex.slice(1, 3), 16);
      const g = parseInt(hex.slice(3, 5), 16);
      const b = parseInt(hex.slice(5, 7), 16);
      return `rgba(${r}, ${g}, ${b}, ${a})`;
    }
    return `rgba(10, 10, 10, ${a})`;
  }

  function loop() {
    update();
    draw();
    requestAnimationFrame(loop);
  }

  initAgents();
  loop();
</script>

<style>
  .page-container {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: calc(var(--nav-height) + 2rem) 1.5rem 3rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--primary);
    text-shadow: var(--glow-md);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .intro {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  /* Terminal window */
  .terminal-window {
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--panel-bg);
  }

  .terminal-titlebar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    background: rgba(var(--primary-rgb), 0.06);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
  }

  .window-dots {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .dot {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .dot-red { background: #ff5f57; }
  .dot-yellow { background: #ffbd2e; }
  .dot-green { background: #28c840; }

  .terminal-title {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .terminal-body {
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    position: relative;
  }

  #sim-canvas {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    cursor: none;
  }

  #sim-canvas:hover {
    cursor: none;
  }

  /* Controls */
  .controls-panel {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: var(--panel-bg);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  }

  .controls-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem 2rem;
  }

  .slider-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .slider-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    white-space: nowrap;
    min-width: 140px;
  }

  .slider-value {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--primary);
    min-width: 45px;
    text-align: right;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  input[type="range"] {
    flex: 1;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    appearance: none;
    height: 4px;
    background: var(--panel-border);
    border-radius: 2px;
    outline: none;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    appearance: none;
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--primary);
    cursor: pointer;
    box-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(var(--primary-rgb), 0.5);
  }

  input[type="range"]::-moz-range-thumb {
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--primary);
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
    box-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(var(--primary-rgb), 0.5);
  }

  input[type="range"]::-moz-range-track {
    height: 4px;
    background: var(--panel-border);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .reset-btn {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    background: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .reset-btn:hover {
    color: var(--primary);
    border-color: var(--primary);
  }

  /* Math section */
  .math-section {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--primary);
    text-shadow: var(--glow-md);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .math-block {
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: var(--panel-bg);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .math-heading {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .math-text {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .math-text + .math-display {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .math-display + .math-text {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .math {
    color: var(--primary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .math-display {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--primary);
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0.6rem 0;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* Mobile */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .terminal-body {
      aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
    }

    .controls-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .slider-label {
      min-width: 120px;
    }

    #sim-canvas {
      cursor: default;
    }
  }
</style>
